          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Italy‚Äôs security dilemma</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent stated that the first trading agreement will likely be awarded to India.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Italy's defense spending remains below the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-04-2025-h2-3-nato-target-of-2-percent" target="_blank">NATO target of 2%</a> of GDP. Rome has not explained how it will meet PM Giorgia Meloni‚Äôs commitment to reach this goal this year. While Meloni asserts support for Ukraine, many Italians on both the left and the right feel indifferent. Her coalition partners think that higher military spending conflicts with social programs.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Italy opposed the EU's plans to fund ammunition trades and a $45B military package for Kyiv. With old arms stocks nearly gone, the 2025 parliamentary approval for aid to Ukraine provides little clarity on actual deliveries.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Monetary issues, high liabilities, and a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-04-2025-h2-4-strong-pacifist-movement" target="_blank">strong pacifist tradition</a> in Italy make defense a sensitive subject. Nevertheless, Italy has advanced defense industries, holds NATO leadership roles, and has strong ties with the US. These advantages could enhance European defense, support Ukraine‚Äôs military, and maintain Washington's engagement in NATO.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          To achieve this, Rome needs a solid 2% plan. Analysts recommend that Italy balance military resource allocation and invest in defense, autonomous systems, and strategic airlift. They followed this with a national campaign to reshape defense as an economic and technological advantage rather than a political burden.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
